    "body": "### Problem\n\ncmdline cursor position does not update when <C-Left>/<C-Right> are mapped via vim.keymap.set()/vim.api.nvim_set_keymap\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nUsing `vim.keymap.set()` in command-line mode reproduces the issue:\n\n```lua\nvim.keymap.set('c', '<Esc>b', '<C-Left>',  { noremap = true, silent = true })\nvim.keymap.set('c', '<Esc>f', '<C-Right>', { noremap = true, silent = true })\n```\n\nIn : command-line mode, the position does not update correctly.\n\nUsing vim.cmd does not have this issue:\n\n```lua\nvim.cmd([[\n  cnoremap <Esc>b <C-Left>\n  cnoremap <Esc>f <C-Right>\n]])\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nvim.keymap.set should behave the same as vim.cmd\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\n/\n\n### Operating system/version\n\narchlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
